SOKOTO – Abubakar Isa, the Youth Leader of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Wurno Local Government area of Sokoto State on Thursday urged youths in the country to vote for President [pro_ad_display_adzone id=”10″] Goodluck Jonathan in February’s general election.
Isa told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Sokoto that a vote for Jonathan would ensure continuity in the provision of people oriented projects across the country.
According to him, the administration has placed high premium in developing the capacity of Nigerian youth to become useful to themselves and the society.
Isa cited the establishment of the new universities across the country as one of the steps taken by the Federal Government to prepare the youths for the future.
He said apart from developing the human capacity, the institutions had generated employment to thousands of unemployed Nigerians.
The youth leader therefore urged all Nigerians to vote for the PDP to ensure good governance.
Isa cautioned the youths against engaging in violence throughout the period of the election so as not to scuttle the nation’s democracy. (NAN)